\p
\v 11 But when Peter cameÂŠ126140 to AntiochÂŠ126144, I had to oppose himÂŠ126147 to his faceÂŠ126146, becauseÂŠ126149 he'd messed up.
\v 12 He'd been eating with non-Jews, butÂŠ126170 when Yacob and his companions arrived, he about-faced and started eating separately, becauseÂŠ126154 he was afraid of \add being criticised by\add* the strict Jews.
\v 13 The other Jews with himÂŠ126179 were also being hypocritesâso much so that even BarnabasÂŠ126187 joined theirÂŠ126190 hypocrisyâ
\v 14 butÂŠ126193 when I sawÂŠ126195 that they weren't beingÂŠ126213 honest with the truthÂŠ126201 of the goodÂŠ126203 messageÂŠ126203, I had to say to Peter in front of everybody, âIf you Jews are livingÂŠ126220 more like non-Jews, and not like \add strict\add* Jews, how can you force non-Jews to obey all the Jewish traditions?â
\s1 You can't be saved by obeying rules
\rem /s1 Jews and Gentiles Are Saved by Faith
\p
\v 15 We follow Jewish laws, not other nations' customs,
\v 16 but we know that we're not saved by following rules,\x + \xo 2:16: a \xt Psa 143:2; Rom 3:20; \xo b \xt Rom 3:22.\x* but only by faith in Yeshua the messiah. So we've believedÂŠ126258 in Yeshua the messiah so that we can be made guiltless by our faith in the messiah, and not by obeying all those rules, becauseÂŠ126269 none of those rules can ever make any personÂŠ126241 guiltless.
\v 17 However, if we attempt to be made guiltless through the messiah, yet find that we're sinnersÂŠ126290, does that mean that the messiah is a servantÂŠ126294 to sinÂŠ126293? That could never be so!
\v 18 If I rebuild what I've already torn down, that would show me to be a law-breaker.
\v 19 \x + \xo 2:19: \xt Rom 6:1-11; 7:1-6.\x*It was the law that showed me that I needed die to the idea of following the law, so that I could liveÂŠ126315 \add to serve\add* \nd GodÂŠ126314\nd* \add instead\add*. I was executed on a post along with the \nd messiahÂŠ126316\nd*,
\v 20 and I'm not living any more, butÂŠ126319 it's the \nd messiahÂŠ126326\nd* now living in me. The way thatÂŠ126336 my bodyÂŠ126332 stays alive now is by living by faithÂŠ126334 in God's sonâthe one who lovedÂŠ126344 me and allowed himselfÂŠ126348 to be executed for me.
\v 21 I'm not rejectingÂŠ126352 God's graceÂŠ126354, becauseÂŠ126358 if the law could make me guiltless, that would mean that the \nd messiahÂŠ126363\nd* diedÂŠ126365 unnecessarily.
\c 3
